# Chart Component Rules

## Structure

Every chart component follows this pattern:

1. Import `BaseChart`, shared types, and theme defaults
2. Define a `Props` type with simple, readable fields
3. Build the ECharts `option` object inside `useMemo`
4. Return `<BaseChart option={option} ... />`

```tsx
import { useMemo } from "react";
import { BaseChart } from "./BaseChart";
import { DEFAULT_COLORS, VARIANT_CONFIG } from "../../utils/theme";
import type { ChartSize, ChartVariant } from "../../types/chart";
import type { EChartsOption } from "echarts";

export type MyChartProps = ChartSize & {
  title?: string;
  // simple props here — no raw ECharts config exposed
  variant?: ChartVariant;
  colors?: string[];
  className?: string;
  loading?: boolean;
};

export function MyChart({ title, variant = "default", colors = DEFAULT_COLORS, className, loading, width, height }: MyChartProps) {
  const option = useMemo<EChartsOption>(() => {
    const v = VARIANT_CONFIG[variant];
    return { /* build option from props */ };
  }, [/* all deps */]);

  return <BaseChart option={option} className={className} loading={loading} width={width} height={height} />;
}
```

## Rules

- Never expose raw ECharts config objects as props — translate them into readable fields
- Always use `useMemo` for the option object
- Always include `className`, `loading`, `width`, `height` props via `ChartSize`
- Use `DEFAULT_COLORS` as the default for any `colors` prop
- Use `VARIANT_CONFIG` when the component supports `variant`
- Do NOT modify `BaseChart.tsx` unless fixing a bug in the core wrapper
- After creating a new component, export it from `src/components/charts/index.ts`
